<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">// e movement stuff
    if (e.atFinalPosition(ep) &amp;&amp; shootTimer.get() == 0 &amp;&amp; driveAtPosition) {
      e.shootLust = true;
      shootTimer.restart();
    }
    if (e.atFinalPosition(ep) &amp;&amp; abandonTimer.get() == 0) {
      abandonTimer.restart();
    }
    // TODO adjust the value
    if (abandonTimer.get() &gt; 1.0) {
      e.shootLust = true;
    }
    if (shootTimer.get() &gt; 0.3 || abandonTimer.get() &gt; 1.5) {
      e.shootLust = false;
      e.requestState(RequestState.None);
    }

    if (shootTimer.get() &gt; 0.8 || abandonTimer.get() &gt; 2.0) {
      finished = true; // blame Adam for this brain death
    }
</code></pre>
<p>Without necessarily stepping inside each function, it looks as if it’s resetting the timer when the elevator reaches L4, meaning that it will end 0.8 seconds after the elevator reaches that point.</p>
<p>For future reference, I would highly recommend looking into <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-compositions.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Command Compositions</a> rather than C-style subroutines. It should generally create cleaner commands and make things a little simpler to debug.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T11:46:15.200Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":256,"readers_count":255,"score":61.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":495757,"topic_slug":"every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/command-compositions.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Command Compositions — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second/495757/2","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558200,"name":"","username":"Dex999999999","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dex999999999/{size}/209038_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T12:10:29.108Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks for the reply, but it most definitely isn’t. We’ve logged thru each step of auto and it exits LimelightAutoCmd properly, that timer is supposed to reset when the elevator is in position. It makes sure we shoot for long enough that the coral clears the wheels</p>
<p>And it doesn’t explain this</p>
