</code></pre>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T21:48:03.408Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":153,"readers_count":152,"score":50.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":495757,"topic_slug":"every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":50684,"username":"crueter","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62784,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second/495757/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3558654,"name":"","username":"crueter","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T21:51:18.182Z","cooked":"<p>Try logging the timestamp as well (or the elapsed time from a timer) in those commands–both in <code>initialize</code> and <code>end</code>. This can help you see if it happens between commands or if one particular command is taking too long.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T21:51:18.182Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":148,"readers_count":147,"score":49.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":495757,"topic_slug":"every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":62784,"username":"Dex999999999","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dex999999999/{size}/209038_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50684,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6032 | QDash"},"post_url":"/t/every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second/495757/6","custom_user_title":"6032 | QDash","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3559775,"name":"Adam Bochek","username":"Bochek","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bochek/{size}/2414_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-17T21:11:08.821Z","cooked":"<p>Adding a conclusion for anyone searching in the future.</p>
<p>The mid auto pauses where our fault,  logic in the code was wrong. <a class="mention" href="/u/crueter">@crueter</a> was right about those in his initial posts.</p>
<p>The pause at the beginning of auto still is occurring after a fresh boot or deploy.   This seems to be related to <a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/pathplanner-initial-lag-after-deploying-code/455068">this thread</a> from spectrum.</p>
<p>The drive train seems to have a significant delay at the beginning of auto, and when it does start moving pathplanner is commanding a larger then expected initial velocity.</p>
<p>You can see in the following image two runs of the same path, the first run is after a deploy, the robot is then driven back to the starting location in teleop and a second run is made.</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/c/e/ce9743015f61222820d0e042bbfa7d82708a41c2.jpeg" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="ttAr0OmgBXXJRywOhopf9LXipKW" width="465" height="411"></p>
<p>Adding a small (0.1s) delay as the first command in the auto seems to have resolved this issue.  We are still seeing a delay of about 400-500ms between auto starting and the drive train moving, but the movement is smooth and the robot starts with a “as expected” initial velocity.</p>
<p>As this concern is no longer the lowest hanging fruit to accomplishing our goals this season we’re not going to spend any more time debugging the delay.</p>
<p>Hopefully this helps someone in the future!</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2025-03-17T21:11:08.821Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":109,"readers_count":108,"score":86.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495757,"topic_slug":"every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second","display_username":"Adam Bochek","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/pathplanner-initial-lag-after-deploying-code/455068","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"PathPlanner Initial Lag after Deploying Code","clicks":15}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":50684,"username":"crueter","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/crueter/{size}/258043_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":7271,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"RoboBitz / 2200 Coach"},"post_url":"/t/every-auto-path-waits-half-a-second/495757/7","custom_user_title":"RoboBitz / 2200 Coach","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3585483,"name":"","username":"Dex999999999","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dex999999999/{size}/209038_2.png","created_at":"2025-04-09T18:28:42.292Z","cooked":"<p>The real problem was in setting all the drivetrain motors to brake mode on disabledExit()</p><aside class="quote quote-modi